Angular Mini Projects

This repository contains a collection of small projects developed using Angular. Each project demonstrates different aspects of Angular development, including component-based architecture, API integration, and user interface design.

Projects Overview

1. Movie Search App

The Movie Search App is a simple Angular frontend application that allows users to search for movies using the OMDb API. It retrieves and displays movie details, including:

Title

Release Year

Poster

Features

Search Functionality: Users can input a movie title and fetch relevant details.

API Integration: Uses the OMDb API to retrieve movie data dynamically.

Responsive UI: The interface is designed to work seamlessly across different devices.

Future Enhancements

Advanced Search Filters: Plan to add options to filter results by genre, director, and rating.

Detailed Movie Information: Expand results to include plot summaries, actors, and reviews.

User Authentication: Enable users to save their favorite movies.

Getting Started

Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following installed:

Node.js and npm

Angular CLI

Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/Dmate889/Angular_mini_projects.git
cd Angular_mini_projects

Install dependencies:

npm install

Run the application:

ng serve

Open http://localhost:4200/ in your browser to use the app.
